&lt;div topic=&quot;Dread&quot; level=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Dread:&lt;/b&gt; A dread weapon excels at attacking one type of creature. Against its designated foe, its effective enhancement bonus is +4 better than its normal enhancement bonus. Further, it deals +4d6 points of bonus damage against the foe, and if it scores a successful critical hit against the foe, that creature must make a Fortitude save (DC 27) or be destroyed instantly and turned to dust. (This even affects creatures immune to critical hits or death magic.) To randomly determine a dread weapon's designated foe, roll on the following table.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Caster Level:&lt;/i&gt; 22nd; &lt;i&gt;Prerequisites:&lt;/i&gt; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, Craft Epic Magic Arms and Armor, &lt;i&gt;summon monster IX; Market Price: +&lt;/i&gt;7 bonus.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p/&gt;&lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; cellspacing=&quot;2&quot; frame=&quot;VOID&quot; rules=&quot;ROWS&quot;&gt;

